Sentencas: Here we report the use of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-delta/carbon nanotube (LNF/CNT) hybrids as novel and robust anode catalysts that are in situ fabricated by exposure of nano-scale LNF perovskite oxide catalysts to slightly humidified methane.
Titulo: In situ formation of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-δ-carbon nanotube hybrids as anodes for direct-methane solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: TEM observations confirm the formation of CNTs with the inner diameter and the wall thickness both at approximate to 15 nm.
Titulo: In situ formation of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-δ-carbon nanotube hybrids as anodes for direct-methane solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Combined XRD and EDX analyses show that LNF oxides decompose into a mixture of La2O3, FeNi3 alloy and LaFeO3, where FeNi3 alloy particles have an average diameter of 45 nm, largely exist outside of these CNTs and are surrounded by nano-scale La2O3 and LaFeO3 oxides.
Titulo: In situ formation of LaNi0.6Fe0.4O3-δ-carbon nanotube hybrids as anodes for direct-methane solid oxide fuel cells
